Ecology and conservation. No ecological information is available. Guano mining took place on Redonda from 1869 to about 1920, during which time the island was inhabited. Since then it has been uninhabited, but there are feral goats (
Capra aegagrus Erxleben
) and black rats (
Rattus rattus
) ( Daltry 2007 ), which have almost certainly disturbed the habitat. No individuals have been seen since the holotype was collected.

Etymology. The species name (
redondae
) is a feminine genitive singular noun and refers to the distribution of the species on the island of Redonda .

